Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteHaloFromBlock(25.10)                          deleteHaloFromBlock(25.10)

Name
       deleteHaloFromBlock  - Removes block halo values for specific blocks or
       for all blocks

Syntax
        deleteHaloFromBlock

       [-help]

       [<inst_name> | -allMacro | -allBlackBox | -allCommitPtn  | -allBlock  |
       -allIOPad | -cell <name>]

       Removes  block  halo  values for specific blocks or for all blocks. Use
       this command after running addHaloToBlock.

Parameters
       -allBlackBox
              Specifies the removal of halo values for all black boxes.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -allBlock
              Specifies the removal of halo values for all blocks.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -allCommitPtn
              Specifies the removal of halo values for  all  committed  parti-
              tions.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -allIOPad
              Specifies the removal of halo values for all IO pads.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -allMacro
              Specifies the removal of halo values for all hard macros.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell <name>
              Specifies  the  removal  of  halo  values for all instances of a
              cell.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  deleteHaloFromBlock parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man deleteHaloFromBlock

       <inst_name>
              Specifies the block where the halo is to be deleted. You can use
              wildcards (* or ?) for specifying instance names.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command removes block halo values from a hard macro named
       cube32:

       deleteHaloFromBlock cube32

Related Information
              * addHaloToBlock

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

              * Floorplan Menu chapter in the Innovus Menu Reference

